的决定，但它对于我的幸福和创作完整性来说是必要的。”他补充说，这部剧有“潜力”，但与他的愿景不符。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/netflixs-live-action-avatar-the-last-airbender-series-gets-its-first-trailer-104024809.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/netflixs-live-action-avatar-the-last-airbender-series-gets-its-first-trailer-104024809.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 558eb448-0eb6-4a60-9aeb-e646751cb69e</guid><dc:creator>萨拉·菲尔丁</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 10 Nov 2023 10:40:24 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1699620758</ingested><modified> 2023-11-10T12:52:42+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Celebrities]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="879" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/15223cf0-7fa9-11ee-b7ec-1c21c88af12e" width="1175"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="711" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/f546c760-7fc7-11ee-9dba-c2ddd5bdac13" width="1175"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Netflix]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Avatar The Last Airbender]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Avatar The Last Airbender]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Turn 10's Alan Hartman is the new head of Xbox Game Studios]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>在微软<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/activision-blizzard-now-officially-belongs-to-microsoft-125053787.html">对动视暴雪进行重磅收购</a>后，微软的 Xbox 领导地位开始形成。根据<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.gamedeveloper.com/business/turn-10-alum-alan-hartman-designated-new-xbox-game-studios-head#close-modal"><em>Game Developer</em></a>看到的<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:LinkedIn;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=6deefbf2-941b-4156-9f41-a61ebb50d13d&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=LinkedIn&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZrPsnnifHK9O931dBcxl5LZWuNAmwBaBUi9-eMIazEk&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Falan-hartman-2208201_thrilled-to-be-representing-such-an-elite-activity-7127853231728185344-9V4o%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.linkedin.com/posts/alan-hartman-2208201_thrilled-to-be-representing-such-an-elite-activity-7127853231728185344-9V4o/">LinkedIn 帖子</a>，Xbox 游戏工作室的新负责人是 Forza Motorsport 开发商 Turn 10 的前老板艾伦·哈特曼 (Alan Hartman)。 “很高兴能够代表如此精英的游戏创作者担任领导 Xbox 游戏工作室的新角色！”他写了。</p><p> Hartman 自 2005 年以来一直领导 Turn 10，最近担任 Forza 和 Fable 的公司副总裁。他负责监督《极限竞速》系列游戏和 ForzaTech 引擎的发布，该引擎被用于《极限竞速：地平线》和即将推出的《神鬼寓言》重启游戏。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>哈特曼接替<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-01-17-microsoft-taps-minecraft-leader-to-run-game-studios.html">马特·布蒂（Matt Booty）</a> ，后者被提升为游戏内容和工作室总裁。最近更换职位的其他高管包括<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.theverge.com/2023/10/26/23933049/microsoft-reorg-xbox-marketing-ai-leadership-changes">莎拉·邦德 (Sarah Bond)</a> ，她成为 Xbox 22 年历史上第一位黑人总裁。她直接向微软游戏总裁 Phil Spencer 汇报。微软斥资 690 亿美元收购动视暴雪可能会带来更多的重组，因为《使命召唤》、《魔兽世界》、《守望先锋》等游戏现在都属于该公司的管辖范围。鲍比·科蒂克 (Bobby Kotick) 仍担任动视暴雪首席执行官，但将于 2023 年底辞职。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/turn-10s-alan-hartman-is-the-new-head-of-xbox-game-studios-095546957.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/turn-10s-alan-hartman-is-the-new-head-of-xbox-game-studios-095546957.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 75d7c1ab-655f-4f51-b1ba-98cf2654603b</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 10 Nov 2023 09:55:46 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1699609537</ingested><modified> 2023-11-10T09:45:40+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Video Games]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="656" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/2e662560-7fad-11ee-9bf6-e5dcf29596da" width="1184"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="656" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/2e662560-7fad-11ee-9bf6-e5dcf29596da" width="1184"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Microsoft]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Turn 10's Alan Hartman is the new head of Xbox Game Studios]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Turn 10's Alan Hartman is the new head of Xbox Game Studios]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Meta may return to China with the release of a new budget VR headset]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>自<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://techcrunch.com/2009/07/07/china-blocks-access-to-twitter-facebook-after-riots/">2009 年 Facebook 被屏蔽</a>以来，Meta 就一直没有进入中国，但这种情况可能即将改变。据<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:The Wall Street Journal;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=2f007401-3eaa-4237-b69b-54ccbe125502&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=The+Wall+Street+Journal&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy53c2ouY29tL3RlY2gvbWV0YS1zdHJpa2VzLWRlYWwtdG8tcmV0dXJuLXRvLWNoaW5hLWFmdGVyLTE0LXllYXJzLTljNjAxMmE5IiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJlODNmZjFmNS04M2E5LTQ4ZWYtYjE3My00YzQ3ZWYzYzAxZGUifQ&amp;signature=AQAAATKmi7zGD7pIfHrtqlG3uF9e6LxTMhZgbn7_UUp39ZZS&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Ftech%2Fmeta-strikes-deal-to-return-to-china-after-14-years-9c6012a9" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.wsj.com/tech/meta-strikes-deal-to-return-to-china-after-14-years-9c6012a9"><em>《华尔街日报》</em></a>报道，该公司计划通过与视频游戏巨头腾讯的独家协议，在全国发布一款全新的低价版虚拟现实耳机。销售暂定于 2024 年底开始，但一些细节仍需最终确定。</p><p>据报道，这款新耳机将比 Quest 2 更强大，但使用的光学器件质量比 Quest 3 低。更注重预算的耳机也可能在其他地区销售。据报道，Meta 将在耳机销售中占据更大份额，而腾讯则将获得更多内容和服务收入，“如软件订阅和游戏销售”。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>这笔交易将为 Meta 的 VR 部门打开一个巨大的市场，该部门一直在<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/mark-zuckerberg-threads-has-just-under-100-million-monthly-active-users-222548501.html">亏损</a>，当然可以利用这一提振。不过，目前尚不清楚腾讯是否需要政府批准才能销售这些设备。游戏是一项流行的VR活动，但中国严格的规定已经对全球最大的视频游戏公司腾讯产生了<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-10-02-tencent-restructure.html">重大影响</a>。</p><p>对于 Meta 薄弱的 VR 部门来说，中国可能也不是灵丹妙药。 TikTok 母公司字节跳动凭借其<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/pico-4-vr-headset-bytedance-150028514.html">Pico 耳机</a>成为中国虚拟现实领域的领导者，但与 Meta 在其他地方一样，其在中国的销售也陷入困境。据报道，腾讯本身也正处于解散自己的 VR 部门的边缘，但据称，一旦 Meta 交易似乎不可避免，腾讯就将其重新组建起来。本季度全球耳机销量与去年同期相比下降了近 45%。</p><p>如果交易成功，Meta 将在 14 年后重新在中国立足。该公司拥有全球 VR 市场 50% 的份额，索尼的 PlayStation VR2 和 Pico 的 VR 耳机分列第二和第三位。苹果即将推出售价<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-vision-pro-hands-on-a-new-milestone-for-mixed-reality-060943291.html">3,500 美元的 Vision Pro</a>耳机进入市场，但在未来发布<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-may-cut-eyesight-display-and-mac-chip-for-its-cheaper-vision-pro-204548008.html">更便宜的版本</a>之前，它不太可能占据一席之地。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/meta-may-return-to-china-with-the-release-of-a-new-budget-vr-headset-090522700.html?src =rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/meta-may-return-to-china-with-the-release-of-a-new-budget-vr-headset-090522700.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> e83ff1f5-83a9-48ef-b173-4c47ef3c01de</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 10 Nov 2023 09:05:22 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1699619878</ingested><modified> 2023-11-10T12:38:02+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Investment & Company Information]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="1075" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/62e98180-7f9c-11ee-92cb-130cf81a7916" width="1750"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1075" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/62e98180-7f9c-11ee-92cb-130cf81a7916" width="1750"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Meta may return to China after a long absence with a budget VR headset]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Meta may return to China after a long absence with a budget VR headset]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Microsoft briefly blocked employees from using ChatGPT over security concerns]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>据<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:CNBC;elmt:;cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34e37b9c-8975-48da-aa39-df8bcd5badc3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=CNBC&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5jbmJjLmNvbS8yMDIzLzExLzA5L21pY3Jvc29mdC1yZXN0cmljdHMtZW1wbG95ZWUtYWNjZXNzLXRvLW9wZW5haXMtY2hhdGdwdC5odG1sIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIxN2YyMjhjYS1mN2VhLTQzNTUtOGQ5Ni05OTU5ZDJkOGEyMjIifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZ0dmhZ9sQHepTZmvffmO15EJVvm7pxeurAQeedFnC83&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F11%2F09%2Fmicrosoft-restricts-employee-access-to-openais-chatgpt.html" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.cnbc.com/2023/11/09/microsoft-restricts-employee-access-to-openais-chatgpt.html"><em>CNBC</em></a>报道，“出于安全和数据方面的考虑”，微软暂时禁止其员工使用 ChatGPT。该公司在内部网站上宣布了这一规则，甚至阻止企业设备访问人工智能聊天机器人。虽然几家科技<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-may-have-restricted-employee-use-of-chatgpt-due-to-privacy-concerns-073141519.html?_fsig=qEkW8utf7caxIZBdfRWvWw--%7EA">公司</a>过去曾<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-tells-employees-not-to-use-ai-tools-like-chatgpt-and-google-bard-114004180.html">禁止</a>（或至少不鼓励）ChatGPT 的内部使用，但微软做同样的事情确实令人好奇，因为它是 OpenAI 最大、最著名的投资者。</p><p>今年1月，微软<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-openai-investment-expansion-152302151.html?_fsig=2pETY7kVMTCj3WfYvTMssQ--%7EA">承诺在未来几年内向ChatGPT的开发商投资100亿美元</a>，此前该公司已向该公司注资30亿美元。它为其产品推出的人工智能工具（例如<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-brings-bings-ai-chatbot-to-its-ios-and-android-swiftkey-apps-113528183.html">Bing 的聊天机器人</a>）也使用 OpenAI 的大型语言模型。但据报道，微软在其说明中表示，“虽然（该公司）确实投资了 OpenAI，并且 ChatGPT 具有内置保护措施来防止不当使用，但该网站仍然是第三方外部服务。 ”该公司建议员工“谨慎行事”，并补充说，该公司还寻求其他外部服务，包括人工智能图像生成器 Midjourney。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> ChatGPT 微软的禁令出乎意料，但也很快。 <em>CNBC</em>表示，微软在发布故事后迅速恢复了对聊天机器人的访问。据报道，该公司还删除了公告中的相关内容，称其正在屏蔽聊天应用程序和设计软件 Canva。一位公司发言人告诉新闻机构，尽管该公告明确提到了 ChatGPT，但该禁令是一个错误，微软在意识到错误后立即恢复了对它的访问。 “我们正在测试法学硕士的端点控制系统，并无意中为所有员工打开了它们，”一位发言人说。他们补充道：“正如我们之前所说，我们鼓励员工和客户使用 Bing Chat Enterprise 和 ChatGPT Enterprise 等具有更高级别隐私和安全保护的服务。”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-briefly-blocked-employees-from-using-chatgpt-over-security-concerns-080403177.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-briefly-blocked-employees-from-using-chatgpt-over-security-concerns-080403177.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 17f228ca-f7ea-4355-8d96-9959d2d8a222</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 10 Nov 2023 08:04:03 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1699603407</ingested><modified> 2023-11-10T08:03:36+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Finance Trading]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="3437" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/3b5820b0-7f95-11ee-b38f-0e3374b445f4" width="4936"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3437" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/3b5820b0-7f95-11ee-b38f-0e3374b445f4" width="4936"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Justin Sullivan via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[SAN FRANCISCO, CALIFORNIA - NOVEMBER 06: Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella speaks during the OpenAI DevDay event on November 06, 2023 in San Francisco, California. OpenAI CEO Sam Altman delivered the keynote address at the first-ever Open AI DevDay conference. (Photo by Justin Sullivan/Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[OpenAI Holds Its First Developer Conference]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Basically all of Maine had data stolen by a ransomware gang]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>缅因州的国家机构成为网络犯罪分子的受害者，他们利用 MOVEit 文件传输工具中的漏洞，使他们成为受该软件大规模黑客攻击影响的实体名单中的最新成员。政府在发布的有关网络安全事件的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.maine.gov/moveit-global-data-security-incident/">通知</a>中表示，该事件影响了大约 130 万人，基本上构成了该<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.census.gov/quickfacts/fact/table/ME/PST045222">州的全部人口</a>。该州于今年 5 月 31 日首次获知 MOVEit 存在软件漏洞，并于 5 月 28 日至 29 日发现网络犯罪分子能够从该州各机构访问和下载文件。</p><p>虽然被盗数据的性质因人而异，具体取决于他们与特定机构的互动，但通知称，不良行为者窃取了姓名、社会安全号码、出生日期、驾驶执照和州身份证号码，以及纳税人身份证号码。在某些情况下，他们还能够窃取人们的医疗和健康保险信息。超过 50% 的被盗数据来自缅因州卫生与公众服务部，其次是缅因州教育部。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>州政府在得知这一事件后立即封锁了 MOVEit 服务器的互联网访问。然而，由于网络犯罪分子已经能够窃取居民信息，因此它还为 SSN 和纳税人号码遭到泄露的人们提供两年的免费信用监控和身份盗窃保护服务。正如<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://techcrunch.com/2023/11/09/maine-government-data-breach-clop-ransomware/?tpcc=tcplustwitter&amp;guccounter=1&amp;guce_referrer=aHR0cHM6Ly90LmNvLw&amp;guce_referrer_sig=AQAAAMraYD3oy1WHQW6-e7bhmFBiWENgM7E7KwSzwmo8qsf-RrKkfXanFeTBMK62vHTrelH30nriQWIkvXrNOBAzoaTIz6JxrqJbjVXe63r2dJvLHg3R4J_-4TIHT6Th39ICwtWEUa2u7d6LJhlQdbtqXtSCjGaOwzs7kj9HGI7p8mA0"><em>TechCrunch</em></a>指出的那样，Clop 勒索软件团伙被认为是之前报道的事件的幕后黑手，但尚未公布从缅因州各机构窃取的数据。</p><p>克洛普 (Clop) 因早些时候纽约市教育局的一次黑客攻击而受到赞扬，其中约<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/clop-ransomware-gang-obtained-personal-data-of-45000-new-york-city-students-in-moveit-hack-204655820.html">45,000 名学生的信息被盗</a>。不过，利用该漏洞的网络犯罪分子不仅针对政府，还针对世界各地的公司。 <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sony-confirms-data-breach-affecting-nearly-7000-employees-075945888.html">索尼</a>就是其中之一。还有美国政府承包商 Maximus Health Services, Inc，其违规行为是迄今为止<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:;elmt:;cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsImxhbmRpbmdVcmwiOiJodHRwczovL3d3dy5lbXNpc29mdC5jb20vZW4vYmxvZy80NDEyMy91bnBhY2tpbmctdGhlLW1vdmVpdC1icmVhY2gtc3RhdGlzdGljcy1hbmQtYW5hbHlzaXMvIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiIwMDM1NTdjMi1mYWQ1LTRkM2YtOWJhNy05NWI3NGE0YTM4ODQifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAQGCn_Qk8_AmaT8uUNKe2SjmO2I9cDeTdFbC4ZMreXx1&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.emsisoft.com%2Fen%2Fblog%2F44123%2Funpacking-the-moveit-breach-statistics-and-analysis%2F" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.emsisoft.com/en/blog/44123/unpacking-the-moveit-breach-statistics-and-analysis/">与 MOVEit 相关的最大事件</a>。</p><p>美国证券交易委员会已经在<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sec-investigating-moveit-hack-that-exposed-data-of-at-least-64-million-people-163057853.html?_fsig=A1bnSxPIOcpjP0FBgkHaMA--%7EA">调查</a>MOVEit 的创建者 Progress Software，尽管它在 10 月份才刚刚向该公司发出传票，并且仍处于调查的“事实调查”阶段。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/basically-all-of-maine-had-data-stolen-by-a-ransomware-gang-061407794.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/basically-all-of-maine-had-data-stolen-by-a-ransomware-gang-061407794.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 003557c2-fad5-4d3f-9ba7-95b74a4a3884</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Fri, 10 Nov 2023 06:14:07 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1699596811</ingested><modified> 2023-11-10T06:13:36+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Society & Culture]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="2320" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/32a04c70-7f88-11ee-afec-64455c7406d9" width="3424"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2320" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/32a04c70-7f88-11ee-afec-64455c7406d9" width="3424"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Dennis Macdonald via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Augusta Maine State Capitol Building and ststehouse where laws are made or changed]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Augusta Maine Capital]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Apple reaches $25M settlement with the DOJ for discriminating against US residents during hiring]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>美国司法部周四在一份<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.justice.gov/opa/pr/justice-department-secures-25-million-landmark-agreement-apple-resolve-employment">声明</a>中表示，苹果公司将支付 2500 万美元的欠薪和民事罚款，以和解有关其在招聘过程中偏袒签证持有者并歧视美国公民和永久居民的指控。这是司法部根据《移民和国籍法》反歧视条款征收的最大金额。</p><p>问题的核心是由劳工部和国土安全部管理的一项名为“永久劳工认证计划”(PERM) 的联邦计划。 PERM 允许美国雇主为外国工人申请签证，成为美国永久居民。作为 PERM 流程的一部分，雇主必须在显着位置刊登空缺职位广告，以便任何人都可以申请，无论其公民身份如何。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>美国司法部表示，苹果公司没有在其招聘网站上宣传 PERM 职位，从而违反了这些规定，并且还要求邮​​寄纸质申请表，从而增加了人们的申请难度，而苹果公司对常规非 PERM 职位则没有这样做。因此，司法部的一项调查发现，苹果公司很少或根本没有收到不需要工作签证的美国公民或永久居民对这些职位的申请。</p><p>美国司法部的声明称，作为和解协议的一部分，苹果公司将支付 675 万美元的民事罚款，并设立一个 1,825 万美元的基金来偿还符合条件的歧视受害者。</p><p>苹果公司不同意司法部的描述。 “苹果公司在美国拥有超过 90,000 名员工，并继续在全国范围内投资，创造了数百万个就业机会，对此感到自豪，”公司发言人<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:CNBC;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=34e37b9c-8975-48da-aa39-df8bcd5badc3&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=CNBC&amp;&amp;signature=AQAAAZ6WkTR5ahFhqCYHs6uhQrtC5YVzrhIYVWYZij4jCfLR&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cnbc.com%2F2023%2F11%2F09%2Fapple-will-pay-25-million-in-doj-discrimination-settlement.html%3Ftaid%3D654d54836fd6760001b433fc%26utm_campaign%3Dtrueanthem%26utm_medium%3Dsocial%26utm_source%3Dtwitter%257Cmain" class="rapid-with-clickid" data-original-link="https://www.cnbc.com/2023/11/09/apple-will-pay-25-million-in-doj-discrimination-settlement.html?taid=654d54836fd6760001b433fc&amp;utm_campaign=trueanthem&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_source=twitter%7Cmain">告诉<em>CNBC</em></a> 。 “当我们意识到我们无意中没有遵守司法部的标准时，我们同意达成和解，以解决他们的担忧。随着我们继续雇用美国工人并在美国发展，我们已经实施了强有力的补救计划，以遵守各个政府机构的要求”</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/apple-reaches-25m-settlement-with-the-doj-for-discriminating-against-us-residents-during-hiring-225857162.html?src =rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/apple-reaches-25m-settlement-with-the-doj-for-discriminating-against-us-residents-during-hiring-225857162.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 0da98cc4-fe2c-4194-b459-e5ce21a5fab5</guid><dc:creator>普拉纳夫·迪克西特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 09 Nov 2023 22:58:57 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1699570871</ingested><modified> 2023-11-09T23:01:15+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Politics & Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Business]]></category><category><![CDATA[Government]]></category><category><![CDATA[Employment & Career]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Pranav Dixit]]></category><media:content height="3231" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-10/0be9b150-6e14-11ee-b7da-ffce9be92d4d" width="4846"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2534" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-11/78c07a30-7f52-11ee-bfd6-8788af036657" width="3763"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[picture alliance via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[PRODUCTION - 27 September 2023, Denmark, Hanstholm: Apple CEO Tim Cook talks to an employee at a solar farm in Hanstholm, Denmark. The solar panels are pa